\begin{proof}
As (2) follows immediately from (1) and the fact that every parameter ideal can be generated by a system of parameters which is a filter regular sequence (cf. \cite[Remark 4.5]{Q13}), it is enough to prove (1). As in the proof of Theorem \ref{T1.2}, we find that the Frobenius action on $H^t_{(\underline{x})}(R)$ is the direct limit of the following commutative diagram:

